Current features:

Records from the camera and sends it to a h264 network stream.

Resources:

http://picamera.readthedocs.org/en/latest/recipes1.html - PiCamera capturing example code
http://fossies.org/dox/Python-2.7.8/classsocket_1_1__socketobject.html#abe96e0334e72cd111557dd9bec0e12bb - python _socketobject class ref
http://www.tornadoweb.org/en/stable/guide/structure.html - Tornado for web server
http://api.mongodb.org/python/current/api/gridfs/ - GridFS docs

FFMPEG command to copy H264 video into an MP4 wrapper:
ffmpeg -i "cameraFront Door-2014-12-01 00:53:22.250299.h264" -vcodec copy -movflags faststart test.mp4

Info on piping in and out of FFMPEG: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10400556/how-do-i-use-ffmpeg-with-python-by-passing-file-objects-instead-of-locations-to

server deps:

pip3 install tornado 

apt-get install mongo mongod python3

ffmpeg built with "--enable-gpl --enable-libx264 --enable-demuxer=mov" options

Useful information for generating subtitles:
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/Apps/Build/Audio_and_video_delivery/Adding_captions_and_subtitles_to_HTML5_video